───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONTEXT
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Same bug pattern as Task 4.7.2 (which fixed RMS). The intent
classifier sets selected_collection to lowercase prefixed values
("hrms_leave_data", "hrms_salarydata", "mrr_general"). But agent
nodes have legacy condition `if selected_collection == "HRMS":`
(or "MRR") at the top of their LLM-binding logic, which is now
always false. Execution falls into the else: branch that sets
full_text = "" and returns silently — empty stream.

This task applies the same fix pattern from Task 4.7.2 to both
HRMS and MRR agent nodes, and adds diagnostic prints.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SCOPE — HRMS
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

In app/workflows/hrms_workflow/nodes.py:

In EACH of creator_agent_node, reviewer_agent_node,
approver_agent_node:

Find the line that says:
    if selected_collection == "HRMS":

Change to:
    if selected_collection and selected_collection.lower().startswith("hrms_"):

Then add this print at the very start of each function (just
after the docstring, BEFORE any other code):

    print(
        f"[DIAG-HRMS] <function_name> entered. "
        f"emp_no={state.get('emp_no')}, "
        f"selected_collection={state.get('selected_collection')!r}, "
        f"selected_agent_role={state.get('selected_agent_role')!r}, "
        f"will_enter_hrms_branch={bool(state.get('selected_collection', '').lower().startswith('hrms_'))}",
        flush=True
    )

Replace <function_name> with the actual function name.
If a DIAG print already exists at the top, replace it with this one.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
